tickets.py    List, create, view, reply, change-status, assign
forms.py      WTForms (validation + CSRF tokens)
security.py   Argon2id hashing, login_required / role_required
db.py         SQLite connection (parameterised), flask init-db
schema.sql    users / tickets / replies tables
seed.py       Creates DB + demo agent & customer
config.py     Env-driven config (secrets, cookie hardening)
templates/    Auto-escaped Jinja2 views
static/       CSS (no inline styles/scripts, CSP-clean)
requirements.txt, README.md, .env.example, .gitignore
```

**Roles & access:** customers register, open tickets, and reply on their own; agents see all tickets, assign, change status (`open→pending→resolved→closed`), and reply. Customers hitting another customer's ticket get a `404` (so existence isn't revealed).

## How to run (port 5062)

```powershell
pip install -r requirements.txt
copy .env.example .env      # then set SECRET_KEY
python seed.py              # builds helpdesk.db + demo users
python app.py               # serves http://127.0.0.1:5062
```

Demo logins: `agent@example.com` / `AgentPass123` and `customer@example.com` / `CustomerPass123`.

## Security requirements — how each is met

- **SQL injection:** every query uses `?` placeholders; no string-built SQL anywhere.
- **Passwords:** Argon2id (salted, memory-hard) via `argon2-cffi`, with transparent rehash-on-login.
- **Access control / IDOR:** ownership checked server-side against the *session* user id, never a client param; agent-only routes guarded by `role_required`.
- **XSS:** Jinja2 autoescaping throughout, strict CSP (`script-src 'self'`, no inline), user text rendered via `white-space: pre-wrap` — never `|safe`.
- **CSRF:** `Flask-WTF` `CSRFProtect` on all POSTs; tokens on every form including logout.
- **Input validation:** WTForms validators (required, length, email, allowed-value regex) reject bad input pre-DB.
- **Session cookies:** `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (auto-relaxed only in debug so HTTP localhost works); session cleared on login to prevent fixation.
- **Security headers:** CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS over HTTPS.
- **No leaked errors:** custom 400/403/404/413/500 pages; tracebacks logged server-side only; debug off by default.
- **Secrets:** `SECRET_KEY` and DB path read from env / `.env`; nothing secret hardcoded.

